# No Barrel Index Exports for Dependency-Injected Classes

This rule establishes a **MANDATORY** prohibition against exporting classes decorated with dependency injection decorators (`@Injectable()`, `@Controller()`, `@EventHandler()`) from barrel index files (`index.ts`). This prevents circular dependencies, ambiguous import paths, and dependency injection container resolution issues.

## Core Principle: Direct Imports for DI Classes

**Classes registered in the DI container MUST be imported directly from their source files, NEVER from barrel index files.**

## Rationale

Barrel index files that re-export DI-registered classes create multiple critical problems:

### 1. Circular Dependency Issues

When classes import each other through barrel files, the import chain becomes opaque, making circular dependencies harder to detect and resolve.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD - Circular dependency hidden by barrel files
// apps/api/src/admin/events/index.ts
export { EventsController } from './controllers/events.controller'

// apps/api/src/admin/categories/index.ts  
export { CategoriesController } from './controllers/categories.controller'

// EventsController imports from barrel
import { CategoriesController } from '@admin/categories' // Loads entire module
// CategoriesController imports from barrel
import { EventsController } from '@admin/events' // CIRCULAR!
```

### 2. DI Container Resolution Problems

The dependency injection container may resolve classes from the wrong import path, causing:
- Multiple instances of the same class
- Injection failures
- Runtime errors that are hard to debug

```typescript
// ❌ BAD - DI container confusion
// File A imports: import { UserRepository } from '@user'
// File B imports: import { UserRepository } from '@user/infrastructure/persistence/prisma/user.repository'
// Result: Container may register TWO different instances!
```

### 3. Ambiguous Import Paths

Multiple ways to import the same class creates maintenance burden and inconsistency:

```typescript
// ❌ BAD - Three different ways to import the same class
import { CategoriesController } from '@admin/categories'
import { CategoriesController } from '@admin/categories/application/controllers'
import { CategoriesController } from '@admin/categories/application/controllers/categories.controller'
```

### 4. Tree-Shaking and Bundle Size Issues

Barrel exports prevent bundlers from properly tree-shaking unused code:

```typescript
// ❌ BAD - Importing one class loads entire module
import { CategoriesController } from '@admin/categories' 
// This loads:
// - CategoriesController
// - ALL use cases
// - ALL repositories  
// - ALL services
// Even if you only need the controller!
```

### 5. Unclear Dependencies

Barrel exports hide the true dependency graph, making it harder to understand module relationships and refactor code safely.

## Strict Rules

### MUST NOT Export from Index Files

**FORBIDDEN**: Exporting any class decorated with DI decorators from `index.ts` files.

#### Classes with `@Injectable()` decorator:

```typescript
// ❌ FORBIDDEN in index.ts

// Repositories
export { CategoryPrismaRepository } from './infrastructure/persistence/prisma/category-prisma.repository'
export { EventRepository } from './infrastructure/persistence/event.repository'

// Use Cases  
export { CreateCategoryUseCase } from './application/use-cases/create-category.use-case'
export { UpdateCategoryUseCase } from './application/use-cases/update-category.use-case'

// Domain Services
export { EventScoringService } from './domain/services/event-scoring.service'

// Application Services
export { CategoryValidationService } from './application/services/category-validation.service'
```

#### Classes with `@Controller()` decorator:

```typescript
// ❌ FORBIDDEN in index.ts

// Controllers
export { CategoriesController } from './application/controllers/categories.controller'
export { EventsController } from './infrastructure/controllers/events.controller'
export { AdminEventsController } from './application/controllers/events.controller'
```

#### Classes with `@EventHandler()` decorator:

```typescript
// ❌ FORBIDDEN in index.ts

// Event Handlers
export { EventCreatedHandler } from './application/handlers/event-created.handler'
export { UserRegisteredHandler } from './application/handlers/user-registered.handler'
```

#### Any class injected into the DI container:

```typescript
// ❌ FORBIDDEN in index.ts

// Any class that will be passed to @Inject() decorator
export { CustomService } from './services/custom.service'
export { DataProcessor } from './processors/data.processor'
```

### MAY Export from Index Files

**ALLOWED**: Exporting types, interfaces, DTOs, enums, and constants that are NOT instantiated by the DI container.

```typescript
// ✅ ALLOWED in index.ts

// Type exports (not classes)
export type { CreateCategoryDto, UpdateCategoryDto } from './application/dtos'
export type { CategoryFilters } from './application/types'
export type { EventSearchCriteria } from './domain/types'

// Interface exports
export type { ICategoryRepository } from './domain/repositories/category.repository.interface'

// Enum exports
export { CategoryType } from './domain/enums/category-type.enum'
export { EventStatus } from './domain/enums/event-status.enum'

// Constant exports
export { MAX_CATEGORY_NAME_LENGTH } from './domain/constants'
export { DEFAULT_PAGE_SIZE } from './application/constants'

// Pure utility functions (not decorated classes)
export { formatCategoryName } from './utils/formatters'
export { validateEmail } from './utils/validators'
```

